tafsir[12]{c,v,t}:
  54,51,"I had destroyed the likes of you in disbelief from the previous nations. Is there anyone who will take a lesson from this and desist from his disbelief?"
  54,54,"Those who are mindful of their Lord through fulfilling His instructions and refraining from His prohibitions will enjoy in gardens and in flowing streams."
  55,2,"He taught the Qur’ān to people by making its memorization easy and facilitating the understanding of its meanings."
  55,3,"He created man perfectly and formed him in the best manner."
  55,4,"He taught him how to express what is within himself in speech and writing."
  55,7,"He raised the sky above the earth as a roof for it. He established justice on earth and instructed His servants with it."
  55,9,"Maintain the weighing justly between yourselves and do not give short weight or measure when you measure or weigh for others."
  55,10,"He prepared the earth for the creation to settle on it."
  55,11,"It contains trees that produce fruit and date-palms that have receptacles that split open to reveal clusters."
  55,12,"It contains grain with straw like wheat and barley and the different types of grain that you have been provided as food. It contains plants whose fragrances you find to be pleasant."
  55,14,"He created Adam (peace be upon him) from dried clay that has a clatter like that of baked clay."
  55,15,"He created the father of the jinn from a flame that is pure of smoke."